<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1456583" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/images-13.jpeg?resize=640%2C359&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="359" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/images-13.jpeg?w=739&amp;ssl=1 739w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/images-13.jpeg?resize=300%2C168&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/images-13.jpeg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/images-13.jpeg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/images-13.jpeg?resize=200%2C112&amp;ssl=1 200w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Serbian-born coach Bora Milutinovic in marking his 76th birthday has bragged about coaching five different nations to the FIFA World Cup. Milutinovic said it was a great honour taking the Super Eagles of Nigeria, USA, Mexico, China, and Costa Rica to the global soccer fiesta, a record he alone can be proud of. He is the first football manager to take four nations past the group stage at the World Cup. “When I am coaching in a country, I feel almost like I become a citizen of that country. “This was the same in Mexico and Nigeria and even China. I look closely at the traits of the people and what moves them, and I try to respond to these things,” he told FIFA.com “But for me, there is nothing like the World Cup. To bring a team to the ultimate – to that level – there’s no feeling like it in the world.” Vanguard For a country which craves World Cup experience, it is fitting that one of the tournament's greatest ever coaches, Bora Milutinovic, now calls Qatar home. The "Miracle Worker" is the man who was a penalty shootout away from taking Mexico to the semi-finals in 1986, saw his Costa Rica team… August 31, 2016 In "Sports" Former Super Eagles Technical Adviser, Bora Milutinovic, still harbor strong feelings for the Chinese team at the on-going Asian Cup in Doha. January 14, 2011 In "Sports" Former Super Eagles Coach Bora Milutinović has given the Golden Eaglets tips on how they can conquer Africa at the CAN U-17 Championship, holding next month in Morocco. March 28, 2013 In "Sports"